Inquisitor	KEY:Background ~ Inquisitor	SORTKEY:Background_1	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Background.Background Selection.SpecialQuality	ABILITY:SKILL|AUTOMATIC|Investigation|Religion	ABILITY:INTERNAL|AUTOMATIC|Tool Proficiency ~ Thieves' tools	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Artisan Tool Proficiency|1	TEMPLATE:Background ~ Inquisitor		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Background Characteristics ~ Inquisitor	ABILITY:Background Feature|AUTOMATIC|Inquisitor ~ Legal Authority	DESC:Historically, inquisitors were cathar detectives who investigated crimes both mundane and supernatural. They were known for traveling to remote parishes plagued by unexplained murders, and for exposing werewolves living among normal humans. During Avacyn’s absence, when the archangel was trapped within the demonic prison known as the Helvault, the inquisitors led a series of brutal forays into Kessig and the Gavony Moorland. They executed suspected lycanthropes with little or no proof, and punished accused heretics in unsanctioned trials. With Avacyn’s madness, this savage form of inquisition has become the norm, and inquisitors who still pry into dark mysteries have become a minority.	ASPECT:BENEFIT|Skill Proficiencies: Investigation, Religion - Tool Proficiencies: Thieves’ tools, one set of artisan’s tools of your choice - Equipment: A holy symbol, a set of traveler’s clothes, and a belt pouch containing 15 gp

Legal Authority	KEY:Inquisitor ~ Legal Authority		SORTKEY:Background	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Class Feature.Background Feature	DESC:As an inquisitor of the church, you have the authority to arrest criminals. In the absence of other authorities, you are authorized to pass judgment and even carry out sentencing. If you abuse this power, however, your superiors in the church might strip it from you.


